 Purpose

This workflow will silently install Oracle Client on the target system.


 Usage Instructions

Review the input parameters listed below, and create a deployment using values appropriate for your environment. This workflow is intended to run on the primary database server.

 Required Inputs

 Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
 Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
 Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
 Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
 Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
 DB IP Address - Required\: IP address of the target for the new tnsnames.ora entry.
 DB Port - Required\: TCP/IP port of the target for the new tnsnames.ora entry.
 Download Filename - Required\: The name of the file to be downloaded from the software repository.
 Download Location - Required\: Location where file will be downloaded to or are pre-staged already.
 Oracle Base - Required\: The fully-qualified path to the Oracle base directory.
 Oracle Group - Required\: The OS group of the Oracle user. Not used for Windows.
 Oracle Home - Required\: The fully-qualified path to be used as the Client Oracle Home installation.
 Oracle Hostname - Required\: The Oracle hostname. Not used for a Windows client installation.
 Oracle User - Required\: The OS user to run the Oracle client. Not used for Windows.
 Server.Become Routine - No description
 SID - Required\: SID for the entry to be added to the tnsnames.ora file.
 Staging Directory - Required\: The fully-qualified directory where the Oracle binaries will be staged.
 TNS Alias - Required\: TNS Alias for the entry to be added to the tnsnames.ora file.

 Optional Inputs

 Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
 Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
 Download From SA - Download binaries from SA (True || False). Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 SA Folder Path - Location of binaries on SA. Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]

 Results verification

To verify client is installed attempt to connect using sqlplus to the remote database setup with the installation of the client.



 Additional Documentation

Additional information about HP Database and Middleware Automation is available on HP Live Network\:

"http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation"\:http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation

To access the documentation, click the RESOURCES link and enter your HP Passport credentials.
